<item>
            <title>[SEC-1129] FilterChainProxy. Not matching ant url when a parameter contains /</title>
                <link>https://jira.spring.io/browse/SEC-1129</link>
                <project id="10040" key="SEC">Spring Security</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;I am using Filter proxy to add several filters to my pages&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;p&gt;&amp;lt;security:filter-chain-map path-type=&quot;ant&quot;&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;lt;security:filter-chain filters=&quot;filtroLoginAutomatico,filtroLogin,filtroBase ...&quot; pattern=&quot;/*&lt;b&gt;/&lt;/b&gt;.html*&quot;/&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;lt;/security:filter-chain-map&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The * at the end is because some pages have GET parameters. The problem comes when one of those parameters, constains a / character (Text is already escaped with javascript escape function). In that case, the page is not matched. It may be solved, adding a new filter-chain&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;lt;security:filter-chain-map path-type=&quot;ant&quot;&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;lt;security:filter-chain filters=&quot;filtroLoginAutomatico,filtroLogin,filtroBase ...&quot; pattern=&quot;/*&lt;b&gt;/&lt;/b&gt;.html*&quot;/&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;lt;security:filter-chain filters=&quot;filtroLoginAutomatico,filtroLogin,filtroBase ...&quot; pattern=&quot;/*&lt;b&gt;/&lt;/b&gt;.html*/*&quot;/&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;lt;/security:filter-chain-map&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Notice the &lt;b&gt;/&lt;/b&gt; at the end of the second chain&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I think it&apos;s a bug, as the / character is in the parameter string and not in the url.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>windows xp sp2&lt;br/&gt;
Eclipse 3.4&lt;br/&gt;
Tomcat 5.23</environment>
